Three people were killed during a robbery at a gun range in Georgia on Friday. The owner of Lock Stock & Barrel Shooting Range in Grantville was found dead along with his wife and grandson, the Grantville Police Department said in a statement. At least 40 weapons and a camera DVR were stolen from the gun range. “Let’s keep Richard Hawk and Family in our prayers,” the department said in a statement. The Georgia Bureau of Investigation and the federal Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Explosives are investigating the crime. Police do not have a suspect in custody, and have asked the public for help in identifying two Ford trucks seen at the range from 5:30 to 6:30 p.m.